2026-04-21 01:27:08 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Battery inside power supply module'] hypothesis_explanation='All measured voltages in the PSU (across battery terminals, LED branch, and external output cables) are 0 V, yet continuity from the output cables into the internal circuit and through the LED resistor is nominal. This shows the wiring and series elements are intact but the source providing potential difference is absent. The only component that can create the 12 V is the internal battery; if it is dead/open, the entire circuit will sit at an undefined but equal potential so every node measures 0 V relative to ground, exactly as observed. No evidence suggests polarity inversion or a downstream fault, since even the PSU indicator LED branch never sees voltage. Therefore, the most probable single root cause is a failed (discharged or open-circuit) battery in the power supply module.'
